Source: pg-kpart
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/hexacluster/pg_kpart

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-kpart
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-kpart
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Reject full partition scans that omit the partition key
 pg_kpart installs a PostgreSQL planner hook that rejects queries which would
 scan every partition of a partitioned table without a usable partition-key
 predicate. It is loaded through shared_preload_libraries or
 session_preload_libraries.
